    <p>As a general rule, accept all gift aid first (grants and scholarships), then subsidized loans if needed, then work-study, and finally unsubsidized loans. Parent PLUS loans and private student loans should be the last resort due to their higher interest rates and less favorable repayment terms. Never borrow more than you need — the total amount you borrow for your entire degree should ideally not exceed your expected first-year salary after graduation.</p>

